{{Quote|Do you remember Miracle Meriko? Now that was a musician's musician. I wonder whatever happened to that old music man. If you want to leave your mark on the galaxy, friend, you gotta study the works of the masters who came before you.|An entertainer|<ref name="SWG">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=terminal|Entertainer|A Musical Legend}}</ref>}}
'''Miracle Meriko''' was a [[Musician/Legends|musician]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], and into the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] whose song "[[Stardance]]" reached number two on the charts in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]]. He eventually [[Death/Legends|died]] while under [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] custody in [[6 BBY/Legends|6 BBY]] with a [[Bounty/Legends|bounty]] of 20,000 [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] on his head. His death was part of the Empire's sweep to eradicate "questionable" artistic enterprises.

